cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the identification and prevention of covert channels in communicating agents, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses the mathematical framework of Communicating Concurrent Kleene Algebra (C 2 KA), which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper discusses the modification of system agents, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
